# SiteSync PM — Product Genome v1.0
<!-- GENOME-VERSION: 1 -->
<!-- LAST-EVOLVED: 2026-04-05 -->
<!-- COMPLETION: 34% -->

## Strand 1: Product Vision

SiteSync PM is the first construction project management platform built as a learning organism.
Target user: Superintendent managing 2 to 5 active job sites simultaneously.
Win condition: A super on a job site can handle an RFI from their phone in under 60 seconds.

Core Identity: AI native, field first, beautifully simple.
Brand promise: The construction OS that builds itself smarter every night.

## Strand 2: Architecture Laws

**Law 1:** React 19 + TypeScript + Vite. No framework changes without ADR in DECISIONS.md.
**Law 2:** HashRouter for routing. All routes defined in App.tsx.
**Law 3:** Inline styles using design tokens from `src/styles/theme.ts`. No CSS modules, no Tailwind.
**Law 4:** Primary Orange #F47820 for all CTAs, active states, brand accent.
**Law 5:** Dark Navy #0F1629 for sidebar background. Always.
**Law 6:** Teal #4EC896 for success states and positive indicators.
**Law 7:** Every page has metric cards at the top with icon, value, and trend.
**Law 8:** Every table row is hoverable and clickable.
**Law 9:** Skeleton loaders within 100ms of navigation. Never a blank screen.
**Law 10:** Empty states are designed and contextual. Never "No data found."
**Law 11:** Error states use toast + inline retry. Never a full page error for a single fetch.
**Law 12:** All pages must be usable at 375px width (iPhone SE).
**Law 13:** Touch targets minimum 44x44px per Apple HIG.
**Law 14:** First Contentful Paint under 1.5s on 4G. Time to Interactive under 3s.
**Law 15:** Zero critical/serious axe core accessibility violations.
**Law 16:** Supabase for backend. RLS policies enforce permissions server side.
**Law 17:** Every feature must have a measurable acceptance criterion before implementation begins.
**Law 18:** The spec is always read before code is written. The spec is always updated after code is verified.
**Law 19:** No feature ships with mock data. No exceptions.
**Law 20:** NEVER use hyphens in UI copy, text content, or comments.

## Strand 3: Feature Genome

### Gene: Dashboard / Command Center
- **Expression Status:** 60% expressed (partial phenotype)
- **Completion Target:** 100% — all metrics live from Supabase, zero mocks
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - [ ] Weather widget: OpenWeatherMap API, schedule impact calculation
  - [ ] AI Insights: Claude API calls, not mock responses
  - [x] Project cards render from database
  - [ ] Sub 100ms response on all widget loads
  - [ ] Real time updates via Supabase subscriptions
  - [ ] Skeleton loaders match final layout geometry
  - [ ] Empty state designed for zero projects
- **Formal Properties:**
  - PROP-001: Dashboard renders with empty database without throwing
  - PROP-002: All data shown matches live Supabase query results
  - PROP-003: No component unmounts with pending network requests
- **Tests Required:**
  - Unit: `dashboard.test.tsx` — renders with no data
  - E2E: `dashboard.spec.ts` — all widgets visible, no errors
  - A11y: axe core zero violations
- **Shadow Mode:** AI pre generates dashboard insights before user opens page

### Gene: RFI Management
- **Expression Status:** 45% expressed
- **Completion Target:** 100% — full CRUD, ball in court tracking, 14 day SLA surfacing
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - [ ] Create, read, update RFIs from Supabase
  - [ ] Ball in court indicator (GC vs Architect vs Supplier)
  - [ ] 14 day response SLA countdown visible on every RFI
  - [ ] Filter by status, priority, assignee, due date
  - [ ] Mobile: 3 tap RFI creation from field
  - [ ] Offline draft support with sync on reconnect
  - [ ] Photo attachment from device camera
- **Formal Properties:**
  - PROP-010: RFI status transitions follow valid state machine (Open > Under Review > Answered > Closed)
  - PROP-011: SLA calculation is always (created_date + 14 days) minus current_date
  - PROP-012: Ball in court assignment changes only on status transition
- **Tests Required:**
  - Unit: `rfi.test.tsx` — CRUD operations, state machine validation
  - Property: `rfi.property.test.ts` — SLA calculation for all valid date ranges
  - E2E: `rfi.spec.ts` — full creation to closure flow

### Gene: Submittals
- **Expression Status:** 40% expressed
- **Completion Target:** 100% — full tracking with ball in court, revision history
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - [ ] Submittal log with ball in court tracking
  - [ ] Revision history with diff view
