  - PROP-021: Approval status cannot skip states
- **Tests Required:**
  - Unit: `submittals.test.tsx` — CRUD, revision tracking, approval workflow
  - Property: `submittals.property.test.ts` — revision monotonicity, state skip prevention
  - E2E: `submittals.spec.ts` — create submittal, upload revision, approve flow

### Gene: Schedule
- **Expression Status:** 25% expressed
- **Completion Target:** 80% — Critical path summary, lookahead, no Gantt (see KILLED_FEATURES.md)
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - [ ] Critical path summary card showing late and at risk activities
  - [ ] 3 week lookahead view
  - [ ] Activity status: Not Started, In Progress, Complete, Late
  - [ ] Predecessor/successor relationships visible
  - [ ] Integration with daily log (auto mark progress)
  - [ ] Mobile friendly list view (not Gantt)
- **Formal Properties:**
  - PROP-030: Critical path calculation uses longest path algorithm
  - PROP-031: Activity completion percentage is bounded [0, 100]
- **Tests Required:**
  - Unit: `schedule.test.tsx` — critical path calc, activity CRUD, status transitions
  - Property: `schedule.property.test.ts` — completion bounds [0,100], critical path correctness
  - E2E: `schedule.spec.ts` — view lookahead, update activity, verify critical path card

### Gene: Budget and Cost Tracking
- **Expression Status:** 50% expressed
- **Completion Target:** 100% — live budget vs actual, change order tracking, variance alerts
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - [ ] Budget summary with original, revised, committed, actual columns
  - [ ] Change order log with approval workflow
  - [ ] Variance alerts at configurable thresholds (default 5%)
  - [ ] Cost code breakdown with drill down
  - [ ] Payment application tracking (AIA G702/G703 format)
  - [ ] Forecast to complete calculations
- **Formal Properties:**
  - PROP-040: Budget total = sum of all line items (no floating point drift)
  - PROP-041: Variance = (actual minus budget) / budget * 100
  - PROP-042: Change order amounts flow through to revised budget automatically
- **Tests Required:**
  - Property: `budget.property.test.ts` — financial calculation invariants
  - Formal: budget calculations formally specified and verified

