### Gene: Files and Documents
- **Expression Status:** 35% expressed
- **Completion Target:** 90% — organized file management with version control
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - [ ] Upload to Supabase storage with folder organization
  - [ ] Version history on all documents
  - [ ] Preview for PDF, images, common formats
  - [ ] Permission based access (respect RBAC)
  - [ ] Bulk download and share
- **Formal Properties:**
  - PROP-130: File version numbers are monotonically increasing per document
  - PROP-131: Deleting a version never removes the latest version
  - PROP-132: Permission based access respects RBAC roles at download time, not upload time
  - PROP-133: Bulk download total size is validated before initiating
- **Tests Required:**
  - Unit: `files.test.tsx` — upload, version history, permission filtering
  - Property: `files.property.test.ts` — version ordering holds across concurrent uploads
  - E2E: `files.spec.ts` — upload file, create new version, verify history and download

### Gene: AI Copilot
- **Expression Status:** 40% expressed
- **Completion Target:** 100% — real Claude integration, context aware, construction domain trained
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - [ ] Real Claude API integration (not mock)
  - [ ] Project context injected into every query
  - [ ] Construction domain knowledge (RFI workflows, submittal processes, AIA forms)
  - [ ] Suggested actions based on project state
  - [ ] Voice input from mobile
  - [ ] Shadow mode: AI generates suggestions before showing to user
- **Formal Properties:**
  - PROP-140: AI responses never expose data from projects the user cannot access
  - PROP-141: Shadow mode prediction is always generated before user sees AI suggestion
  - PROP-142: Claude API timeout (30s) never blocks the main UI thread
  - PROP-143: Project context injection includes only current project data
- **Tests Required:**
  - Unit: `ai-copilot.test.tsx` — API integration mock, context injection, shadow mode
  - Property: `ai-copilot.property.test.ts` — context isolation holds for all project/role combinations
  - E2E: `ai-copilot.spec.ts` — ask question, verify context aware response, check shadow log

