  - E2E: `auth.spec.ts` — login, verify role restrictions, test invite flow

## Strand 4: Quality Invariants (Never Regress)

| Metric | Floor | Current | Trend |
|--------|-------|---------|-------|
| Build passes | 100% | ✓ | → |
| TypeScript errors | 0 | 0 | → |
| Test coverage | >70% | 43% | ↑ |
| Bundle size (initial JS) | <300KB | 287KB | → |
| Accessibility violations | 0 | 4 | ↓ |
| `as any` casts | 0 | 12 | ↓ |
| Mock data in production | 0 | 7 | ↓ |
| Longest response time | <500ms | 340ms | → |

## Strand 5: Competitive Intelligence

| Feature | Procore | Autodesk | SiteSync Target |
|---------|---------|----------|-----------------|
| Mobile RFI creation | 12 taps | 8 taps | 3 taps |
| AI insights | None | Basic summaries | Predictive, Claude powered |
| Offline mode | Partial | No | Full (Capacitor + local cache) |
| Daily log voice entry | No | No | Yes (Whisper transcription) |
| Shadow mode learning | No | No | Yes (Tesla Data Engine model) |
| Setup time for new project | 2 hours | 1.5 hours | 15 minutes (AI assisted) |
| Ball in court tracking | Manual | Manual | Automatic on status change |
